        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ")",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": ",",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the sons of Hagar,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for possession of the pasture-grounds east of Gilead. This Arab nation is mentioned in the Assyrian inscriptions. (The LXX. has ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τοὺς παροίκους",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": ", i.e., haggārîm, u",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " sojourners,” “nomads.”)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They dwelt in their tents.—This phrase first occurs in Genesis 9:27. The Belaites occupied the territory of the Hagarites.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "They dwelt in their tents.",
